CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 14, 1962, pg. A30 reads: "Silver Medal Winners - The Ammon Married Women's volley ball team won the runner-up spot and second place medals last Thursday at the South Side Market House during the annual tournament. Second-best among ten entries (from left), kneeling; Capt. Beatrice Mahaffey, Irene Robinson and Pauline Penix.  Rear: Nettie Myers, Ruth Lucus [sic], Mildred Allen, McInerny Woodson and Delare Hill. - Harris PHoto."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Ammon Center Married Women's volleyball team, from left, kneeling: Beatrice Mahaffey; second row: Irene Robinson and Pauline Penix; rear: Nettie Myers, Ruth Lucas, Mildred Allen, McInerny Woodson, and Delare Hill, posed in interior, possibly South Side Market House
